&gt; It depends what you mean by &quot;testing criteria&quot;. 
&gt; 
&gt; You can extend the TestCase class to have additional assert methods if
&gt; you want to routinely check on different things. For example, I&#39;ve got a
&gt; group of class doing a fair bit of work with reflection. I ended up
&gt; defining a new test base class, and added a method like this:
&gt; 
&gt; public void assertType(Class expectedType, Object o) { 
&gt;   assertNotNull(&quot;Can&#39;t really check the type of a null object&quot;, 0); 
&gt;   assert(&quot;Expected type &lt;&quot; + expectedType.toString() + &quot;&gt;. Actual Type:
&gt; &lt;&quot; + o.getClass().toString() + &quot;&gt;&quot;, 
&gt;          o instanceof expectedType); 
&gt; } 
&gt; 
&gt; Is this the sort of thing you mean? 
